[Student "S"]
{When NORTH opens 2\C SOUTH has enough strength (9 points) for a positive response. But, 
because her suit is \Ds, she must jump to 3\D.

NORTH thinks slam and uses Blackwood to discover that SOUTH holds one Ace. 

That's all SOUTH needs to know to bid 6\D.}

